But, of course, as time goes by,

496
00:30:46,110 --> 00:30:47,779
its concentration on the door side
increases too.

497
00:30:48,446 --> 00:30:50,882
DOOR: 0.32 - WINDOW: 1.22

498
00:30:50,949 --> 00:30:53,484
Now, the third reason.

499
00:30:54,686 --> 00:30:56,287
Kurokawa, now.

500
00:30:56,354 --> 00:30:58,857
MANGANESE - IV - OXIDE CRYSTALS
HYDROGEN PEROXIDE

501
00:31:03,361 --> 00:31:07,298
<i>She added manganese dioxide</i>
<i>to hydrogen peroxide to produce oxygen.</i>

502
00:31:08,933 --> 00:31:10,201
Why now?

503
00:31:10,268 --> 00:31:12,337
You can't produce oxygen beforehand.

504
00:31:12,403 --> 00:31:15,807
After the victim was dead
and before the maid came,

505
00:31:16,474 --> 00:31:19,043
this is how the defendant
managed to stay alive.

506
00:31:34,492 --> 00:31:35,426
CO CONCENTRATION DOOR - 0.82

507
00:32:39,257 --> 00:32:40,091
Mr. Kurokawa!

508
00:32:40,158 --> 00:32:42,293
Wakura! Open the windows for ventilation.

509
00:32:57,241 --> 00:32:58,176
Mr. Kurokawa!

510
00:32:58,843 --> 00:33:00,178
Mr. Kurokawa!

511
00:33:02,747 --> 00:33:03,748
I thought I would die.

512
00:33:06,217 --> 00:33:07,085
Gosh!

513
00:33:12,323 --> 00:33:13,458
The experiment is done.

514
00:33:14,459 --> 00:33:18,663
This is a well-prepared
and planned murder.

515
00:33:20,331 --> 00:33:21,366
I think…

516
00:33:23,835 --> 00:33:27,171
maybe I'm not cut out to be a lawyer.

517
00:33:28,373 --> 00:33:32,176
I knew that when you were
aiming to be a lawyer.

518
00:33:39,017 --> 00:33:40,885
TOKYO DETENTION HOUSE

519
00:33:41,586 --> 00:33:45,857
We did an experiment to see
why you survived in that room.

520
00:33:53,331 --> 00:33:54,198
These.

521
00:33:55,366 --> 00:33:58,236
We found the manganese dioxide
at the bottom of the bedroom's tank.

522
00:34:01,672 --> 00:34:04,008
The state of the room
when your parents passed away

523
00:34:04,809 --> 00:34:07,678
gave you the idea to use the curtain
as a screen, right?

524
00:34:09,313 --> 00:34:14,585
Your life and your brother's life
were saved because of that.

525
00:34:18,890 --> 00:34:20,425
You saw my brother?

526
00:34:21,659 --> 00:34:22,493
We did.

527
00:34:25,797 --> 00:34:26,798
Then,

528
00:34:28,666 --> 00:34:32,703
will you not say that he was saved
after seeing his condition?

529
00:34:37,842 --> 00:34:41,712
My father put a partition screen
there just by chance.

530
00:34:42,480 --> 00:34:43,314
<i>I'm sure that</i>

531
00:34:43,381 --> 00:34:46,584
<i>he just didn't want to see</i>
<i>the children he was going to kill.</i>

532
00:34:48,753 --> 00:34:51,389
<i>But only I survived because he did that.</i>

533
00:34:59,630 --> 00:35:03,434
Didn't I tell you last time
that I am lucky?

534
00:35:04,902 --> 00:35:07,805
It was my luck that I met Norikura
at the club I worked at.

535
00:35:08,806 --> 00:35:11,109
It was my luck that I became his wife too.

536
00:35:12,577 --> 00:35:16,514
I could admit my brother into
a hospital, thanks to him too.

537
00:35:18,182 --> 00:35:19,750
Why did you kill Mr. Norikura, then?

538
00:35:20,985 --> 00:35:22,153
Because he found out.

539
00:35:23,754 --> 00:35:25,590
That jerk said this to me.

540
00:35:27,358 --> 00:35:29,527
He told me to forsake my brother.

541
00:35:29,594 --> 00:35:30,828
MARINA NORIKURA
COMING OUT FROM HOSPITAL

542
00:35:30,895 --> 00:35:32,029
MARINA'S BROTHER IN HOSPITAL

543
00:35:32,096 --> 00:35:36,834
I have no obligation
to support your brother too.

544
00:35:38,136 --> 00:35:41,405
Please! My brother can only rely on me!

545
00:35:41,472 --> 00:35:43,541
Listen, Marina.

546
00:35:43,608 --> 00:35:45,776
I've been using dirty methods,

547
00:35:45,843 --> 00:35:48,779
as dirty as sipping muddy water,
to survive until now.

548
00:35:48,846 --> 00:35:54,085
I like you because you tried to
crawl your way up from the bottom.

549
00:35:54,852 --> 00:35:56,587
That's why I made you my wife.

550
00:35:58,389 --> 00:36:02,493
If you want to stay with me,
ignore the weak, like I do!

551
00:36:02,560 --> 00:36:07,632
Forget your worthless and useless brother!
Do you hear me?

552
00:36:08,499 --> 00:36:09,600
<i>At that time…</i>

553
00:36:10,835 --> 00:36:11,936
<i>I made up my mind.</i>

554
00:36:13,538 --> 00:36:14,939
For my brother…

555
00:36:16,507 --> 00:36:18,376
for my parents, who died because of him,

556
00:36:19,110 --> 00:36:20,511
I would kill him.

557
00:36:22,180 --> 00:36:25,583
I decided to kill him
and take everything away from him.

558
00:36:34,992 --> 00:36:39,497
If you confess your crime, I can
plead extenuating circumstances.

559
00:36:40,798 --> 00:36:43,568
-What are you saying?
-We'll appeal to the judge

560
00:36:43,634 --> 00:36:44,769
why you did that…

561
00:36:45,970 --> 00:36:48,206
and I'll do my best to
reduce the sentence--

562
00:36:48,272 --> 00:36:49,740
Don't be ridiculous!

563
00:36:50,808 --> 00:36:54,845
If you'll do your best,
do it to prove that I'm innocent!

564
00:36:56,981 --> 00:37:00,585
If you realized what I did,
you should know how to deceive them!

565
00:37:00,651 --> 00:37:02,353
Get rid of the evidence and everything!

566
00:37:02,987 --> 00:37:04,188
We cannot do that.

567
00:37:04,956 --> 00:37:06,157
Are you stupid?

568
00:37:07,558 --> 00:37:11,062
Do you know how many deaths
Norikura's scams caused?

569
00:37:12,597 --> 00:37:15,499
That jerk laughed and said this
when he got drunk.

570
00:37:17,001 --> 00:37:19,003
Fourteen people he'd swindled had died

571
00:37:19,070 --> 00:37:20,771
the same way my parents did.

572
00:37:22,707 --> 00:37:25,676
But that jerk wasn't punished.

573
00:37:26,877 --> 00:37:29,880
He got some good lawyers and ran away
because of la ack of evidence.

574
00:37:31,048 --> 00:37:33,818
You can get away with crime
because there's no evidence.

575
00:37:33,884 --> 00:37:35,786
Isn't that the world of law?

576
00:37:36,821 --> 00:37:39,890
You're a lawyer. Why did you do
something uncalled-for?

577
00:37:43,794 --> 00:37:46,397
Because you asked Mr. Yufuin
to defend you.

578
00:37:51,902 --> 00:37:54,138
You actually wanted someone
to realize, didn't you,

579
00:37:55,740 --> 00:37:58,876
the pain of having your family
taken away and this is your revenge.

580
00:37:59,710 --> 00:38:01,779
-So you asked Mr. Yufuin--
-Go!

581
00:38:02,880 --> 00:38:04,015
You don't have to come again.

582
00:38:04,749 --> 00:38:05,783
Marina.

583
00:38:05,850 --> 00:38:07,585
You are fired.

584
00:38:08,686 --> 00:38:10,321
I want you to be saved!

585
00:38:15,159 --> 00:38:16,594
The job of a lawyer…

586
00:38:19,864 --> 00:38:22,333
is to protect the client's benefit,
indeed.

587
00:38:23,601 --> 00:38:24,535
But…

588
00:38:27,305 --> 00:38:30,308
Is turning your back to a crime
you committed and running away…

589
00:38:34,078 --> 00:38:36,113
something that benefits you?

590
00:38:39,684 --> 00:38:41,385
Even if we win the case…

591
00:38:44,355 --> 00:38:45,890
if you still bear the sin…

592
00:38:48,426 --> 00:38:50,094
you will never be saved.

593
00:38:58,336 --> 00:38:59,337
Wait!

594
00:39:06,577 --> 00:39:09,447
Mr. Kurokawa is removed
from his post? Why?

595
00:39:11,982 --> 00:39:13,050
I see.

596
00:39:22,159 --> 00:39:23,594
GONZABURO NORIKURA'S MURDER
DEFENDANT, MARINA NORIKURA

597
00:39:23,661 --> 00:39:25,229
Are they all the documents?

598
00:39:25,296 --> 00:39:27,732
Please take over the case for us.

599
00:39:29,266 --> 00:39:30,935
I'm surprised, though.

600
00:39:31,702 --> 00:39:34,705
I knew that you've been
in charge of this case,

601
00:39:34,772 --> 00:39:37,375
but I never expected her
to dismiss you halfway.

602
00:39:38,509 --> 00:39:41,545
Our plan of defense disagrees
with our client's.

603
00:39:42,780 --> 00:39:46,984
You could almost prove her innocence
due to lack of evidence.

604
00:39:47,051 --> 00:39:48,753
Why did you disagree?

605
00:39:48,819 --> 00:39:52,957
Could it be because Mr. Kurokawa
messed it up again?

606
00:39:53,023 --> 00:39:54,959
-There you go.
-Oh, thanks.

607
00:39:56,727 --> 00:39:57,762
It's hot!

608
00:40:00,731 --> 00:40:02,666
WRITTEN STATEMENT OF EXPERT OPINION

609
00:40:05,970 --> 00:40:07,805
Shred the document.

610
00:40:10,007 --> 00:40:12,076
Don't leak it to the police
or the prosecutor.

611
00:40:12,143 --> 00:40:15,012
If you do that, your life
as a lawyer will really be over.

612
00:40:17,348 --> 00:40:18,783
Why do you look at me like that?

613
00:40:19,550 --> 00:40:21,652
Are you surprised that I worry about you?

614
00:40:22,787 --> 00:40:23,621
No.

615
00:40:24,255 --> 00:40:26,557
It comes with criminal defense cases.

616
00:40:27,358 --> 00:40:31,896
Sometimes the defendant lies to you,
sometimes the result is hopeless.

617
00:40:34,331 --> 00:40:36,434
Corporate law is nice.

618
00:40:37,201 --> 00:40:39,670
You can work for honest workers
and organizations

619
00:40:39,737 --> 00:40:41,505
and the office gains profits too.

620
00:40:42,473 --> 00:40:44,141
I like to do this more.

621
00:41:00,624 --> 00:41:03,294
No, I am not worried about you.

622
00:41:03,360 --> 00:41:06,130
I thought you would really be fired
and I looked forward to it.

623
00:41:06,197 --> 00:41:07,932
But you said you were very worried.

624
00:41:07,998 --> 00:41:08,933
Idiot!

625
00:41:09,867 --> 00:41:10,835
Mr. Kurokawa,

626
00:41:11,435 --> 00:41:14,538
the hospital that Marina's brother
stays at just called.

627
00:41:15,506 --> 00:41:16,740
Yes?

628
00:41:17,274 --> 00:41:19,643
<i>His condition got a lot worse</i>
<i>this morning and…</i>

629
00:41:22,880 --> 00:41:26,851
<i>I contacted Marina's new lawyer</i>
<i>and asked him to tell her.</i>

630
00:41:42,199 --> 00:41:44,134
COURTHOUSE

631
00:41:44,201 --> 00:41:49,039
CLOSING ARGUMENT

632
00:41:51,876 --> 00:41:53,511
Please un-cuff the suspect.

633
00:42:00,718 --> 00:42:05,122
As shown, all the prosecutor's claims
are mere guesses.

634
00:42:05,723 --> 00:42:08,826
Someone is innocent until proven guilty,

635
00:42:08,893 --> 00:42:11,762
which is against
the presumption of innocence.

636
00:42:11,829 --> 00:42:14,331
You actually wanted someone
to realize, didn't you?

637
00:42:14,398 --> 00:42:16,467
<i>I want you to be saved!</i>

638
00:42:16,534 --> 00:42:20,004
<i>If you still bear the sin,</i>
<i>you will never be saved.</i>

639
00:42:21,839 --> 00:42:22,873
For the above reasons,

640
00:42:22,940 --> 00:42:25,309
I claim the defendant, Marina Norikura--

641
00:42:25,376 --> 00:42:26,577
Wait.

642
00:42:27,678 --> 00:42:28,846
What is it?

643
00:42:29,680 --> 00:42:31,415
I want to say something.

644
00:42:31,949 --> 00:42:34,285
There will be time for you to talk later.

645
00:42:34,351 --> 00:42:36,787
Do you call it
a self-confession in this case too?

646
00:42:38,055 --> 00:42:39,490
I want to say what I did.

647
00:42:40,157 --> 00:42:41,492
Self-confession?

648
00:42:43,627 --> 00:42:46,430
I killed my husband.

649
00:42:46,497 --> 00:42:47,631
Hey…

650
00:42:47,698 --> 00:42:48,666
Be quiet!

651
00:42:48,732 --> 00:42:49,767
Be quiet!

652
00:42:49,833 --> 00:42:50,734
What's going on?

653
00:42:50,801 --> 00:42:51,936
What did you say?

654
00:42:52,002 --> 00:42:56,907
Defendant, do you know
what you are talking about?

655
00:42:57,474 --> 00:42:58,342
Yes.

656
00:42:59,310 --> 00:43:03,781
I can explain everything, including
why and how I killed my husband.

657
00:43:03,847 --> 00:43:05,816
Defendant, be quiet!

658
00:43:05,883 --> 00:43:07,318
Your Honor, please adjourn--

659
00:43:07,384 --> 00:43:10,120
-You are fired.
-What?

660
00:43:11,889 --> 00:43:15,025
Will you defend me again?

661
00:43:24,468 --> 00:43:26,737
I thought I needed no salvation.

662
00:43:30,274 --> 00:43:31,108
But…

663
00:43:45,122 --> 00:43:46,991
What made her confess
her crime in court?

664
00:43:47,057 --> 00:43:48,726
It must be Kurokawa again.

665
00:43:49,460 --> 00:43:51,795
Let's do our best to plead
extenuating circumstances.

666
00:43:54,498 --> 00:43:55,666
Mr. Kurokawa.

667
00:43:57,534 --> 00:44:00,938
Did I do the right thing as a lawyer?

668
00:44:02,406 --> 00:44:04,174
Marina made the decision.

669
00:44:05,209 --> 00:44:06,343
Moreover,

670
00:44:06,410 --> 00:44:09,046
if you don't know
whether it was right or not,

671
00:44:09,113 --> 00:44:11,015
that means it could be right.

672
00:44:15,619 --> 00:44:16,587
You're right.

673
00:44:18,822 --> 00:44:20,491
What's the matter?

674
00:44:21,859 --> 00:44:23,861
You haven't had them?

675
00:44:23,927 --> 00:44:25,763
I suddenly want to eat.

676
00:44:27,865 --> 00:44:29,500
Mind your manners.

677
00:44:33,537 --> 00:44:34,772
KAZUTO YUFUIN

678
00:44:34,838 --> 00:44:37,875
I will be in charge of your case
with Yufuin from now on.

679
00:44:40,844 --> 00:44:43,881
I couldn't fulfil my duty 15 years ago,

680
00:44:45,149 --> 00:44:46,150
so, this time,

681
00:44:46,784 --> 00:44:49,086
I hope I can help you.

682
00:44:52,956 --> 00:44:54,625
I am counting on you.

683
00:45:06,103 --> 00:45:07,905
Miss Wakura,

684
00:45:07,971 --> 00:45:10,307
don't be unhappy because
you aren't in charge of her case.

685
00:45:10,374 --> 00:45:11,875
We have other jobs to do.

686
00:45:11,942 --> 00:45:13,343
I know.

687
00:45:13,410 --> 00:45:15,846
And you asked Miss Arima for this, right?

688
00:45:19,049 --> 00:45:21,051
DOCUMENTARY 24, TOUO UNIVERSITY
STUDENT MURDER CASE

689
00:45:23,053 --> 00:45:24,021
THE DRAMA IS FICTITIOUS.

690
00:45:24,088 --> 00:45:25,989
BURNING CHARCOAL IN A CLOSED SPACE
IS DANGEROUS

691
00:45:26,557 --> 00:45:29,827
<i>A death-row inmate imprisoned</i>
<i>for murder 24 years ago</i>

692
00:45:29,893 --> 00:45:30,794
<i>and his daughter.</i>

693
00:45:30,861 --> 00:45:32,496
Don't mess up my life!

694
00:45:32,563 --> 00:45:34,631
<i>You want to file an appeal for a retrial?</i>

695
00:45:34,698 --> 00:45:37,568
<i>Can they save the victims</i>
<i>of the false conviction?</i>

696
00:45:37,634 --> 00:45:41,004
It's unforgivable to take away
their future too.

